<span class="header"><strong>Owner's Policy</strong></span>
</center></center></center></center><br>
<br>
<span class="body">HUD Line 1103 reflects the <u>balance</u> of the charge that it takes to cover just the Owner's policy when a lender’s policy is required. <br>
<br>

<strong>Example Transaction</strong> – $200,000 purchase price with $150,000 loan. If Loan Premium is $300 and Owner’s Premium is $450, then the amount listed on Line 1103 (Owner’s Premium) would be $150 plus the cost of a simultaneous issue policy charge if applicable ($100, for example), for a total of $250.00  <br>
<br>

This way, the borrower knows the actual cost of the required Lender’s Premium, and sees the <u>additional</u> cost of purchasing Owner’s coverage. </span>

